{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> αἴξ</b>, αἰγός, ὁ, <br /> h(: <i>dative</i> <i>plural</i> αἴγεσιν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.486, αἴγεσσιν 4th-5th c.AD: Choeroboscus Grammaticus “Scholia in Theodosii Canones” 323\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also <i>Boeotian dialect</i> ἤγυς, ={αἴγοις}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 7.3171\">Refs</a>]:—<b>goat</b>, mostly <i>feminine</i>, μηκάδας αἶγας[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.124; λεύκας αἶγος 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica 7(assuming variant), compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 71, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 639a, etc., but _masculine_ in 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.106, 530; also τῶν αἰγῶν τῶν τραγῶν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.112:—once in Trag., 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 793 (_anapaest meter_). \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> αἲξ ἄγριος wild <b>goat</b>, probably <b>ibex</b> (compare αἴγαγρος), ἰονθάς[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.50; ἴξαλος 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.105; αἶγες ὀρεσκῷοι 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.155; ἀγρότεραι 17.295:\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] —proverbs, αἲξ οὐρανία in Comedy texts as a source of mysterious and suspected wealth, in allusion to the horn of Amalthea, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 244; οὐράνιον αἶγα πλουτοφόρον “Comica Adespota” 8\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἲξ τὴν μάχαιραν (i.e. ηὗρε), of those who 'ask for trouble', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Zenobius Paroemiographus 1.27\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; αἲξ οὔπω τέτοκεν 'don't count your chickens before they are hatched',[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1.42; αἲξ Σκυρία· ἐπὶ τῶν τὰς εὐεργεσίας ἀνατρεπόντων· ἀνατρέπει γὰρ τὸ ἀγγεῖον ἀμελχθεῖσα 4th-5th c.AD: Diogenianus Paroemiographus 2.33; αἲξ ἐς θάλασσαν· ἀτενὲς ὁρᾷς, ἐπὶ τῶν φιληδούντων 3.8; κἂν αἲξ δάκἡ ἄνδρα πονηρόν 5.87; οὐ δύναμαι τὴν αἶγα φέρειν, ἐπί μοι θέτε τὸν βοῦν 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.830a; ἐλεύθεραι αἶγες ἀρότρων· ἐπὶ τῶν βάρους τινὸς ἀπηλλαγμένων 2nd c.AD: Zenobius Paroemiographus 3.69\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; κατ᾽ αἶγας ἀγρίας, ={ἐς κόρακας}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus, 4th-5th c.AD: Diogenianus Paroemiographus 5.49; νοῦσος, αἶγας ἐς ἀγριάδας τὴν ἀποπεμπόμεθα 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Aetia” 3.1.13\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; αἰγῶν ὀνόματα, of worthless objects, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>the star Capella</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Aratus Epicus 157. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> a water-bird, apparently of the <b>goose</b> kind, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 593b23. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>fiery meteor</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 341b3. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> in <i>plural</i>, <b>waves</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Artemidorus Daldianus Onirocriticus 2.12. (_Attic dialect_ αἶξ, _accusative_ to Hdn.Gr. 1.937.)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G6167","accentedUnicode":"αἴξ","shortDef":"a goat","mediumDef":"a goat","stepGloss":"a goat","stepTransliteration":"aix","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}